European Stocks Drop After Three-Week Rally; Carlsberg Falls, UBS Advances

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-02-21T08:06:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/european-stocks-drop-after-three-week-rally-carlsberg-falls-ubs-advances.html
European stocks retreated after a
three-week rally left the Stoxx Europe 600 Index close to its
highest level since August 2008. U.S. futures and Asian shares
fluctuated.  Carlsberg A/S sank 4.2 percent after the Nordic region’s
biggest brewer reported net income for the fourth quarter that
missed analysts’ estimates. UBS AG gained 0.6 percent after
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. advised buying the shares of  Switzerland ’s biggest bank.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 lost 0.3 percent to 290.04 at 8:05
a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  